data.name: autoLabel17.Text
data.value: Note: When you perform a move step update or add, the walking and sliding move steps (WF, WR, SR, SL, SU and SD) will use the 'Sliding/Walking Step Count' value of the top panel of this application. Looking and rolling move steps (LR, LL, LU, LD, RC and RCC) will use the 'Looking/Rolling Step Angle' value of the top panel of this application.

data.name: autoLabel21.Text
data.value: Capture and store Mandelbulb3D project information into a local database, including the MP3 parameter set, project file locations, keyframe data and screenshots of the Mandelbulb graphics. The goal is to have a local source of information that describes each Mandelbulb3D project that is in the works or that has been completed and published.

data.name: lbl_Admin_JoyToKey_Intro.Text
data.value: The JoyToKey app provides mapping of the keys of a console game controller or a standard PC keyboard to the movement keys of the Mandelbulb3D Navigator. The JoyToKey application allows a liberal period of evaluation at full functionality, and offers a low license fee.

data.name: autoLabel30.Text
data.value: The sample project will create a variety of keyframe records that include various keyframe movements. You will be able to modify the sample keyframe movements with the Move Designer. Of course, this does not create a corresponding project in the Mandelbulb3D application.

data.name: autoLabel34.Text
data.value: In situations where you want a clean start with your data, you can purge the Copilot's database of all records, including all project records and all the keyframe records of each project, as well as all of the Move Sequences if you prefer. To purge all records use the left button below. To keep your Move Sequences use the right button below. You should make a backup of the Copilot database in case purging turns out to be a mistake.

data.name: autoLabel26.Text
data.value: The Mandelbulb3D Animation Copilot facilitates creating Mandelbulb3D animations by mapping a game controller or keyboard keys to the Mandelbulb3D Navigator movement keys and recording those keyframe movements to a local database.
